sub_title: United World College Educated and Educator. IBDP English A teacher, workshop leader and forum moderator.
summary: A proven leader, able to multi-task and problem solve while remaining organized and informed, Ebony is a committed educator with experience in non-profit, urban public and private school settings.  As a supervisor, she is forward thinking and supportive, and believes in providing vision, soliciting and acting on feedback, and collaborating to achieve a goal.  A former international student, she is keenly attuned to the international school experience and easily builds rapport with her colleagues, students and parents.  Ebony is well versed in the English/Language Arts programs of several educational models (US, IGCSE and IB MYP & DP), and is able to be a consistently innovative developer of educational and extracurricular programs for first and second language students.
